data.title: Victoria Memorial, Kolkata
data.meta_description: Victoria Memorial, Kolkata - India - Set in an attractive, well-tended park, the incredible Victoria Memorial is a vast, beautifully proportioned confection of white marble domes. Built to commemorate Queen Victoria’s 1901 Diamond jubilee, the structure was finally finished nearly 20 years after her death. One of India’s greatest buildings. Shot with a Nikon D300S - high res pics would be posted later in my site www.rajivpachat.zenfolio.com
